Extending the RFID Suite

1.1.1 How to develop a new reader


What is a reader ? TBD


A reader is a iPOJO component packaged in an OSGi bundle.


The component requires a [org.osgi.service.event.EventAdmin&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/service/event/EventAdmin.html] service to send [org.osgi.service.event.Event&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/service/event/Event.html] object containing the ALE event.

Here is an example of rfid event sent by a [fictive reader&gt;http://svn.forge.objectweb.org/cgi-bin/viewcvs.cgi/aspire/branches/rfidsuite/readers/bundles/fictive/] to the EventAdmin at the edge level:

* topic: ~~org/ow2/aspirerfid/rfidtopic/rfid~~
* with the following properties:
** event.topics=org/ow2/aspirerfid/rfidtopic/rfid
** publisher.instance.name=fictivereader
** ~~rfid.readerguid~~=fictiveguid
** ~~rfid.readername~~=fictive
** ~~rfid.tagguid~~="357654321000001123456789"
** ~~timestamp~~=1234444400859

Events must be sent on topics matching "org/ow2/aspirerfid/rfidtopic/" in order to be included in ALE reports.

The component provides a javax.management.DynamicMBean service for the Reader configuration (serial port, ethernet port, speed, antenna ...).


Nota Bene:


* The current (ie tags/rfidsuite-200809) version of the component provides a standard MBean service for the Reader Management but is currently moving to iPOJO JMX handler (see below).
* The next version MUST use the iPOJO 1.2.0 [JMX handler&gt;http://felix.apache.org/site/ipojo-jmx-handler.html] to simplity the MBean definition
* The next version MUST also use the iPOJO 1.2.0 [CM handler&gt;http://felix.apache.org/site/configuration-handler.html] to configure the reader
* The next version MUST also use the iPOJO 1.2.0 [EA handler&gt;http://felix.apache.org/site/event-admin-handlers.html] to [post&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/service/event/EventAdmin.html#postEvent(org.osgi.service.event.Event)] events.

1.1.1 How to develop a new sensor

What is a sensor ? A sensor can measure physical data about a identified objects or about the environment in which objects are temporally or permanently. A modern sensor can provide the instaneous measurement. Moreover, it can log the history (limited or cyclic) of the measurements taken periodically. It can also log the history of threshold infringements.

1.1.1.1 WireAdmin-based sensors
In the current version (ie tags/rfidsuite-200809), the driver of a sensor is a iPOJO component packaged in an OSGi bundle. It is attached to the environnement of the indentified objects and collect only the instantaneous measurements.


The component provides a [org.osgi.service.wireadmin.Producer&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/service/wireadmin/Producer.html] service to push/update sensor data. The type of sensor data (called [flavors&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/service/wireadmin/WireConstants.html#WIREADMIN_PRODUCER_FLAVORS] in the [WireAdmin&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/service/wireadmin/package-summary.html] terminology) is not limited to a list but it must be Comparable. Typical classes are [org.osgi.util.measurement.Measurement&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/util/measurement/package-summary.html],  [org.osgi.util.position.Position&gt;http://www.osgi.org/javadoc/r4v41/org/osgi/util/position/package-summary.html], [javax.microedition.location.Location&gt;http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=179], java.lang.Double,  java.lang.Float,  java.lang.Long ...


The Producer service should have the following registration properties : 
* ~~application~~ represents the application (eg application=outdoor temperature)
* ~~org.osgi.util.measurement.Unit~~ represents the SI unit if the flavor is org.osgi.util.measurement.Measurement (eg org.osgi.util.measurement.Unit=K)
* ... other ??? TODO

Warning : You'd better prefer SI (International System) units such as meter for distance, meter/second for speed, radian for angle, etc for your modelized data.

Producers are automatically wired to consumers using the WireAdminBinder.

Nota Bene:
* The current version  (ie tags/rfidsuite-200809) of the component provides a javax.management.DynamicMBean service for the Sensor Management.
* The next version MUST use the iPOJO 1.0.0 [JMX handler&gt;http://felix.apache.org/site/ipojo-jmx-handler.html] to simplity the MBean definition
* The next version MUST also use the iPOJO 1.0.0 [CM handler&gt;http://felix.apache.org/site/configuration-handler.html] to configure the sensor

